&lt;p&gt;The Financial Planning &amp;amp; Analysis (FP&amp;amp;A) team plays a critical role in supporting the company’s financial and strategic initiatives through data-driven insights and operational planning. As an integral member of the corporate FP&amp;amp;A team, the Financial Planning &amp;amp; Analysis (FP&amp;amp;A) Analyst will play a key role in supporting The Trade Desk’s headcount and expense planning functions.&amp;nbsp; We are looking for a team player who will provide exceptional financial support and promote financial discipline across parts of the organization.&amp;nbsp; In this role, you will create financial reports to review with cross-functional leaders to help manage their budgets and refine forecasting.&amp;nbsp; You will help drive continued development of financial processes to facilitate improvements in our global cost forecasting accuracy, accountability, and transparency.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with FP&amp;amp;A team to drive financial accountability by improving the budgeting and forecasting process; refine budget/forecast reporting and templates that will help leaders manage their respective divisions for continued profitable growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn and expand the use of our new budgeting and reporting systems; suggest process improvements as the tool user base expands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with department level reporting to support management decisions to ensure execution of company goals and drive accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve capital forecasting and reporting/tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform value added ad-hoc analyses that help drive decision making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Accounting team to assist in various close procedures including variance fluctuation analysis, accruals, and other deep-dive analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously take on additional responsibility to improve processes and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in FP&amp;amp;A, corporate finance, or accounting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel and financial modeling skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of financial statements (including US GAAP) and forecasting concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical mindset with high attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate across teams in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and proactive with a willingness to learn&lt;/li&gt;
